
The '''Shitalakshya River''' originates as a [[distributary]] of the [[Brahmaputra River]] and flows southwest and then east of the city of [[Narayanganj]] in central [[Bangladesh]] until it merges with the [[Dhaleshwari River]] near Kalagachhiya. The river is about 110 km long and at it widest, near Narayangani, it is 300 meters in width. It remains navigable year round.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://banglapedia.search.com.bd/HT/S_0353.htm
|title=Shitalakshya
|publisher=banglapedia
|accessdate=2007-07-06
}}
</ref>

